name: sfchronicle
text:
COVID-19 hospitalizations rose slightly in the Bay Area as local health departments recorded 693 patients as of August 14, an increase of 16 from the day before.

Hospitalizations across California fell slightly to 5,112 on Saturday, a decrease of 77.

https://t.co/OjY8oOL9WS

name: sfchronicle
text: “I did not feel safe at my job. I was concerned about endangering my family to COVID-19 through my exposure at work to personnel who were not strictly adhering to social distancing guidelines and the safety protocols I had written.” https://t.co/t5aEUPgCVa

name: sfchronicle
text: With the Bay Area’s most elite dining rooms closed, restaurants have been offering luxe, elaborate meals on nearby farms in the hope of staying in business. https://t.co/UZVh3XR34x

text:
Here's the report from the 49ers’ first practice of training camp, from @Eric_Branch. One standout was rookie running back JaMycal Hasty, who "was enjoyable to watch as he jitterbugged down the field on each of his three carries."

text: Update: California energy grid managers said they do not expect more rolling blackouts Saturday, even after PG&E warned that additional outages could be required. https://t.co/M4fzsvmvrT
